   }
}

## Response Elements
<a name="API_waf_GetGeoMatchSet_ResponseElements"></a>

If the action is successful, the service sends back an HTTP 200 response.

The following data is returned in JSON format by the service.

 ** [GeoMatchSet](#API_waf_GetGeoMatchSet_ResponseSyntax) **   <a name="WAF-waf_GetGeoMatchSet-response-GeoMatchSet"></a>
Information about the [GeoMatchSet](API_waf_GeoMatchSet.md) that you specified in the `GetGeoMatchSet` request. This includes the `Type`, which for a `GeoMatchConstraint` is always `Country`, as well as the `Value`, which is the identifier for a specific country.  
Type: [GeoMatchSet](API_waf_GeoMatchSet.md) object

